Influencers.name: Malvika Subba
Influencers.details: Malvika Subba is a well-known media figure with a large following in the country. She is a self-assured and independent lady who wears several hats in the media. She has been an outspoken supporter of Hami Nepal since its inception. She frequently shares our fund-raising messages on her many social media channels.

Influencers.name: Shristi Shrestha
Influencers.details: Shristi Shrestha is a Nepalese film actress and Miss World 2012 winner who works in Nepali cinema.She is WWF Nepal's eighth Young Conservation Ambassador and works with WWF Nepal on Snow Leopard conservation programs. She made a donation and shared our fundraising posts. She has also participated in ration giving programs with Hami Nepal

Influencers.name: Priyanka karki
Influencers.details: Priyanka Karki is a Nepalese cinema actress, model, and director who is widely acknowledged as the industry's most recognizable face. During the formation of the plasma bank, she took the initiative and assisted with the awareness campaign

Influencers.name: Abhaya Subba
Influencers.details: Nepalese singer, composer, and musician Abhaya Subba. She is the front woman for the band Abhaya & the Steam Injuns. She is noted for her creative music and social activities. She supported us with the work we carried out during COVID 19's second wave. She also helped with the fundraising efforts by reaching out to friends in other countries. She criticized news sites who questioned Hami Nepal's efforts. She often shares our fundraising announcements and has a link to our GoFundMe page in her Instagram bio. She is constantly praising Hami Nepal's efforts

Influencers.name: Samragee RL Shah
Influencers.details: Samragyee Rajya Laxmi Shah, better known by her stage name Samragyee RL Shah, is a Nepalese film actress. Shah has received various awards, including a National Film Award and a number of National Film Development Council National Film Awards. During the COVID outbreak, the team formed a Enough is Enough civil rights movement to raise awareness of the government's complete failure. Following the demonstration, the youngsters staged a Satyagraha hunger strike, in which the president of Hami Nepal, Mr. Sudan Gurung, also took part, to bring awareness about our government's inefficiency. During the demonstration and the Hunger Strike, Samragyee used her social media networks to broadcast all of the content in real time, delivering vital information to her big following.

Influencers.name: Shrinkhala Khatiwada
Influencers.details: Miss Nepal World 2018 Shrinkhala Khatiwada is a Nepalese model who studied Architecture at the Institute of Engineering, Pulchowk Campus and is currently pursuing her master's degree in Harvard University. She competed in Miss World 2018 and received the Beauty with a Purpose Award along with multimedia award. Shrinkhala donated the money to our organization that she acquired from her beauty with a purpose grant. Since Hami Nepal had actively been working as a frontline worker representing the youth population of our country during the tragic second wave of COVID-19, she posted all of Hami Nepal's information on social media, praising and even visited the Hami Nepal office for moral support

Influencers.name: Niti Shah
Influencers.details: Niti Shah is the 2017 Miss International Nepal winner. She was named the most popular face of EnVogue and the first runner-up in Face's House of Fashion 2013, and she is unquestionably Nepal's most popular model. She gathered money from her friends and family and contributed it. During the covid epidemic in Nepal,  also volunteered to visit a covid positive patient and give an oxygen concentrator.

Influencers.name: Raju Lama
Influencers.details: Raju Lama is a Nepalese singer and songwriter from Sindhupalchok. He is the lead singer of Mongolian Heart, a musical group. Songs in Nepali, Tibetan, Tamang, and other languages are included in his work. Since our Enough is Enough campaign, Raju Lama has been a big proponent of the Hami Nepal team. He encouraged his friends to attend the protest and used social media to disseminate our appeal to his followers. During the 2020 Hunger Strike, he kept in touch with our President Sudan Gurung and offered moral support. In the years thereafter, he has demonstrated a strong interest in the work of Hami Nepal. During the severe flash flood in Sindhupalchowk, Raju Lama also made a monetary donation to Hami Nepal to aid in the reconstruction of homes in the affected areas

Influencers.name: Swastima khadka
Influencers.details: Swastima khadka is one of the most popular actresses of Nepal. She has made her contribution with Hami Nepal by constantly sharing our fundraising posts and participating in ration giving programs.

Influencers.name: Paramita Rana
Influencers.details: Paramita Rajya Laxmi Rana is a Nepalese actress, model, singer, and makeup artist. Since the Hunger Strike and the Enough is Enough campaign, Paramita has been a strong supporter of Hami Nepal. She supported our President Sudan Gurung, who actively participated in the Satyagraha Hunger Strike, to express her moral support. Since then, she has routinely shared our content and information with her tens of thousands of followers on various social media channels

Influencers.name: Lex Limbu
Influencers.details: Lex Limbu (Nepal, 1992) is a well-known Nepali blogger and entrepreneur. As of 2016, he manages lexlimbu.com, a blog, and Tracing Nepal, a tour and sightseeing company. Since Earthquake 2015, Lex has been a strong proponent of our team's efforts. During that period, he encouraged his friends and followers to show their support for the team in various ways. Lex has also expressed his support in COVID-19 through social media, posting all of the material and assisting us in raising funds through his friends and followers during the first and second waves. Lex has been continually informing his overseas acquaintances about our work, which has been extremely beneficial to Hami Nepal.

Influencers.name: Jyotsna yogi
Influencers.details: Jyotsna Yogi is an actress, model, and television personality. She is most recognized as the face of 'the house of fashion.' She has made a donation of medications to Hami Nepal. She also assisted Hami Nepal with its awareness campaign during the plasma bank's creation.

Influencers.name: Aditi Budhathoki
Influencers.details: Aditi Budhathoki is a Nepalese model and actress who was born on June 28, 1996 (age: 24 as of 2020) in Damak, Jhapa, Nepal. Aditi has relocated to India in order to pursue her aspirations. In 2017, she starred in Sandeep Brar's Punjabi music video Step Cut. In 2018, she made her acting debut in the film Kri. Since the Enough is Enough campaign in 2020, Aditi Budhathoki has been a consistent supporter of Hami Nepal, sharing all of our informative content and fundraising campaign among her massive followers on social media platforms.

Influencers.name: Lemi Tamang
Influencers.details: Lemi Tamang works as a professional make-up artist and social media influencer. She's shared our fundraising posts across all of her social media accounts. Her talent was put to good use to help Hami Nepal generate funds. She assisted with our 'Thopa thopa le bancha samundra' fundraising effort by teaching live make-up classes and allocating funds

Influencers.name: Avishek K.C.
Influencers.details: Avishek KC is regarded as one of Nepal's metal music pioneers. He is the frontman for the bands Underside and Equals, as well as the vocalist and guitarist for theactnepal. Avishek K.C. is also a part of the Metal for Nepal' organization. Our President Sudan Gurung regards Avishek KC as a good friend. Despite their closeness, he has been extremely supportive of the team since the Satyagraha hunger strike in 2020. During the Hunger Strike, he offered moral support to our president and used his social media platform to raise his voice. Hami Nepal also worked on various projects with his organization Metal for Nepal, including Manang Vaccination and Dashain Sabai ko Lagi. Avishek KC has also given Hami Nepal a substantial cash donation to support our initiatives

Influencers.name: Albatross
Influencers.details: Albatross are a Kathmandu-based Nepalese rock band. Albatross, a three-piece student band formed in 1998, has built a name for themselves in Nepali music. All Nepalese were hit hard by COVID-19's second wave. Following a period of adversity, Hami Nepal rose to the occasion and took a significant stride toward resolving COVID-19's problems. Albatross raised finances after launching a new album through an app called Noodle, and the team was collecting funds through different mediums. All of the money raised through the Noodle app was donated to Hami Nepal to aid in the fight against COVID-19.

Influencers.name: Suzeena Shrestha
Influencers.details: Suzeena Shrestha is a singer-songwriter from Nepal. When the epidemic invaded Nepal in 2020, the government demonstrated its incompetence, prompting youths to stage a Satyagraha hunger strike. After a while, their health deteriorated and they were admitted to the hospital due to weakness, but that didn't stop the youths from speaking out, as Suzeena stepped in as a replacement and participated in a relay Hunger Strike, supporting the other participants and raising awareness for our country's citizens. Suzeena has been a big proponent of the team since the beginning, regularly sharing our fund-raising campaign as well as useful content with her enormous following.

Influencers.name: Elena Gurung
Influencers.details: Elena Gurung is a viner and a content developer. She makes videos for her YouTube channel, collaborates with other YouTubers, makeup artists, and collaborates with other brands in addition to making content for her Instagram. Elena has also been one of Hami Nepal's most ardent supporters since its inception. She has aided us by disseminating our fund-raising campaign and our information to her large following on social media. Elena also volunteered with our team at Teaching Hospital during the mass vaccination.

Influencers.name: The Elements
Influencers.details: Drummer Dipesh Gurung, guitarist Raunaq Singh Adhikari, and vocalist and songwriter Ishan Raj Onta established the Elements band in late 2016. Drum and Roll brought these three youngsters together through a similar project. They collaborated to compose music, develop films, and record songs because they had a deep love for music. The Element has used its social media platform to share Hami Nepal's messages, which has inspired many young people. During the second wave of COVID-19, The Elements also organized a virtual concert to generate funds for Hami Nepal, which has been a huge assistance in keeping up with our projects. They also assisted with delivering flood reliefs to lamjung when our team was aiding in sindhupalchowk

Influencers.name: Sydney Gurung
Influencers.details: Sydney Gurung is an Instagram model and influencer. She has volunteered in our civil rights movement entitled “Enough is Enough”, and shares our fund- raising messages on her social media.

Influencers.name: Reshma Ghimire
Influencers.details: Reshma Ghimire is a Nurse, Nepali model and actress known for her Amazing Personality, Beautiful Appearance,Adorable Smile and versatile acting. Since our team was unable to reach many parts of Nepal, Reshma Ghimire, who was staying in Biratnagar during the second wave of COVID-19, actively assisted COVID patients from Biratnagar by constantly sharing their needs on her social media platform. Her initiative aided a large number of patients, as her large following stepped up to assist those in need. Regardless, she has supported us by posting our fund-raising drive and all of our content with her social media following.

Influencers.name: Aakriti Rajbhandari
Influencers.details: Akriti Rajbhandari is a professional make-up artist and social media influencer.She has shared our fundraising postings on her social media channels, and she has also given cash raised by thrifting her clothes.

Influencers.name: Parakram Rana
Influencers.details: Parakram Rana is a youthful, attractive, and passionate blogger and stylist. He also performs photoshoots and video editing. LGBTQ community members in Nepal remain in the shadows owing to societal fear. However, he is open about his sexuality since being homosexual has served as an inspiration to many people. He promoted our fundraising messages on social media and contributed his YouTube profits.

Influencers.name: Sanna Gurung
Influencers.details: Sanna Gurung is a YouTube sensation who rose to stardom owing to her self-titled channel. Her fashion, lifestyle, and beauty vlogging have earned her a following. When a big flash flood ravaged Manang in 2021, Hami Nepal decided to support the residents in the vicinity. Sanna provided a substantial donation to aid Hami Nepal with the initiative during that period. Sanna has also always been a strong supporter of Hami Nepal's team, sharing both the fund-raising operation and Hami Nepal's messages
